HEADWORD: Sarum use
<hw>Sa"rum use`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Ch. of Eng.)</fld> <def>A
liturgy, or <xex>use</xex>, put forth about 1087 by St. Osmund, bishop
of <xex>Sarum</xex>, based on Anglo-Saxon and Norman customs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

